summary: there’s nothing like a little pain to remind you you’re alive
title: there’s nothing like a little pain to remind you you’re alive
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2LmnRei

by foxxwrites

(an alternative to endgame cause it made me sad, alexa play breathe by taylor swift.
don’t take this too seriously i just wanted a happy ending.)

“Thanos eviscerated half of the entire population of Earth,” Banner rests his forehead between his pointer finger and thumb.
Jane’s mouth falls open, “He what? Where were his parents? Who brought him up to think that’s okay?”
“Jane, he is not a nice man, he probably killed them.”
“Thor, that’s not how you comfort someone.”
“Oh, yes, they were probably asleep and felt nothing,” Thor smiles, nodding at Jane, then turns to wink at Steve.
“Wow, and I thought I was oblivious,” Rocket shakes his head.
Scott jumps up, “No! He is perfectly aware—” Rhodey slaps his hand over Scott’s mouth and smiles.
